# dnd_mud core and UI

## Layered architecture

```
ui/  →  core/  →  database/ (YAML)
```

- **UI** (`ui/menus.py`, `ui/input_handler.py`) — отображение и ввод; без бизнес-логики
- **Core** (`core/`) — модели, механика, локализация; не зависит от UI
- **Data** (`database/`) — YAML; core читает через свои модули

UI must not access database files directly.

## Localization

All user-facing strings via localization — never hardcode:

```python
from core.localization import get_string, load_strings

strings = load_strings(language)
message = get_string(strings, "menu.new_game")  # ✅
message = "New Game"                            # ❌
```

Keys use dot notation (`menu.new_game`). Update both `database/strings/ru.yaml` and `en.yaml`.

## D&D mechanics

- Models in `core/models.py` — `dataclass` for `Character`, `Adventure`
- Use `Enum` for character classes, not raw strings
- Explicit condition checks; named constants from YAML (no magic numbers)
- Effects apply/remove explicitly — no hidden state

```python
if character.character_class == CharacterClass.WARRIOR:  # ✅
if character.class_name == "warrior":                    # ❌
```

## Pre-commit checklist

- [ ] Strings localized in `ru.yaml` / `en.yaml`
- [ ] Type hints on public APIs
- [ ] No duplicated damage/effect logic (DRY)
- [ ] Docstrings on public functions
